Detailed technical content (by TOC item)

1. Pipeline overview and mapping
MISSION.md -> supervisor -> dispatch workflows -> Issue -> Code -> Test -> PR -> Merge
- Supervisor role: LLM supervisor gathers repository context (issues, PRs, workflow runs, features) and dispatches workflows strategically.
- Workflows are GitHub Actions using the Copilot SDK to make targeted code changes.
- Execution flow: write mission in MISSION.md; push to main; supervisor creates feature issues; agent workflows open PRs and run tests; human or automated merge completes change.
- Key implementation requirement: maintain test workflow (test) and ensure status checks are selectable in branch protection.

2. Required secrets and exact scopes
- COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN
  - Type: Fine-grained personal access token (PAT)
  - Required scopes: GitHub Copilot Read permission (scoped token for Copilot SDK use)
  - Purpose: Authenticates with the Copilot SDK for all agentic tasks
- WORKFLOW_TOKEN
  - Type: Classic personal access token (PAT)
  - Required scopes: workflow scope
  - Purpose: Allows init.yml and workflows to update .github/workflows/ files (note: GITHUB_TOKEN cannot modify .github/workflows/)

3. Repository settings and permissions (exact settings to set)
- GitHub Actions: Allow all actions (Settings → Actions → General → Allow all actions)
- Workflow permissions: Read and write permissions (Settings → Actions → General → Workflow permissions = Read and write)
- Allow GitHub Actions to create PRs: Checked (Allows workflows to open PRs)
- GitHub Discussions: Enabled (Settings → General → Features → Discussions enabled) — used by discussions bot

4. agentic-lib configuration keys and valid values (extracts and concrete options)
- schedule.supervisor
  - Allowed values: off | weekly | daily | hourly | continuous
  - Typical recommendation: daily (production adjust to hourly/continuous as needed)
- paths.mission
  - Example: "MISSION.md"
- paths.source
  - Example: "src/lib/"
- paths.tests
  - Example: "tests/unit/"
- limits.feature-issues
  - Integer: maximum concurrent feature issues (example: 2)
- limits.attempts-per-issue
  - Integer: max retries per issue (example: 2)
- execution.build/test/start
  - Build: npm run build (default in package.json)
  - Test: npm test (Vitest)
  - Start: npm run start
- tuning.model
  - Example: gpt-5-mini (supported options: gpt-5-mini | claude-sonnet-4 | gpt-4.1)

5. Install / update commands (exact CLI commands)
- Manual update of agentic infra: npx @xn-intenton-z2a/agentic-lib@latest init
- Typical developer flow: write MISSION.md → git push main → supervisor workflow runs automatically

6. Branch protection and CI selection (concrete recommendations)
- On main branch: require pull request reviews before merging (protect main)
- Require status checks to pass: include the test workflow (select the workflow named test)
- Additional recommended checks: linter, formatting and any static analysis workflows

7. Operational responsibilities and workflow behaviour
- init.yml updates: init workflow can update agentic infra and runs daily by default; manual re-init uses the npx init command above.
- Workflows use two different token types for different capabilities; ensure tokens are stored in repository secrets and have the exact scopes above.
- The supervisor aggregates repository context and decides which workflows to dispatch; ensure Issues, PRs, and Discussion permissions are enabled for full operation.

SUPPLEMENTARY DETAILS (technical specifications and implementation details)

Secrets storage and usage
- Add secrets via Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
- COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN value must be a fine-grained token with Copilot Read permission; store as COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN
- WORKFLOW_TOKEN must be a classic PAT with workflow scope; store as WORKFLOW_TOKEN

Action permissions and consequences
- If Workflow permissions are not set to Read and write, workflows will be unable to create or update issues/PRs programmatically.
- If Actions are restricted (not "Allow all actions"), third-party actions or market actions used by the agentic infra may be blocked.

