Best practices and implementation patterns
- Keep MISSION.md small, explicit, and test-oriented; the supervisor uses it as a single source of intent.
- Ensure unit tests exist for any functionality to be modified by agents; mark test workflow as a required status check in branch protection.
- Use fine-grained PAT for COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN to follow least-privilege principle; regenerate periodically.
- Use WORKFLOW_TOKEN only for repository bootstrap tasks; restrict its usage and rotate frequently.
- Keep agentic-lib.toml in repo root and update schedule in low-risk increments (daily → hourly) after validating in staging repositories.

Troubleshooting procedures (step-by-step)
1. Workflows not creating or updating workflow files
   - Verify WORKFLOW_TOKEN exists and has workflow scope; check that init.yml used it.
   - Confirm repository Actions settings allow workflows to update workflow files (classic PAT required).
2. Agentic workflows failing authentication with Copilot SDK
   - Verify COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN is a fine-grained PAT with Copilot Read permission and not expired.
   - Check Actions log for specific 401/403 errors and validate token scopes.
3. Agent PRs created but tests fail
   - Open failing workflow run; run npm test locally and reproduce failing test to produce a fix.
   - Ensure the test workflow is selected as required status check in branch protection.
4. Init workflow not updating infra on schedule
   - Check init.yml schedule in .github/workflows/ and verify workflow run history.
   - Run npx @xn-intenton-z2a/agentic-lib@latest init locally to force update and inspect output.

